<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1292] Multiple migrations might run at once</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1292</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The service.MigrationManager class manages a MIGRATION_STAGE where nodes should execute db.migration.Migration instances.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that the node that a client connects to via Thrift or Avro initiates the migration in their client thread (calls migration.apply). Instead, the Thrift and Avro clients should ensure that the migration occurs in MIGRATION_STAGE, and should block until the migration is applied by the stage.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
